QUALIFICATION: Neave, 1940, Nomenclator Zoologicus, 4: 321, has an entry for Stomatia Lamarck, 1799, Mémoires de la Société d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris, (an VII): 77; Lamarck (1799) used Stomatia without an author, but Lamarck, 1801, Système des animaux sans vertèbres: 96, placed Stomatia phymotis in Stomatia, so it is clear that Lamarck did not intend to establish a different name. Stomata [Gray, 1821, London Medical Repository, 15: 232] and Stromatia [Griffith & Pidgeon, 1834, The animal kingdom arranged by... Cuvier, 12: 86] are incorrect subsequent spellings. See also Stomax

Not made available by Inaba & Oyama (1977) Catalogue of the molluscan taxa described by T. Habe: 43 (G. millegranosa cited as type species, but no diagnosis); nor from Beu & Ponder (1979) Records of the Australian Museum 32(1): 9 (G. millegranosa cited as type species by original designation, but no diagnosis and Galeoastraea listed in synonymy of Bolma)
